Consider an open economy in which the exchange rate is ﬁxed and equal to 1.
Let
consumption (C), investment (I), taxes (T), government expenditure (G), imports (IM),
and exports (X) satisfy the following:
C = 20 + 0.8(Y −T);
I = 10;
G = 10;
T = 10;
IM = 0.3Y ;
X = 0.3Y ∗
where Y and Y ∗denote domestic output and foreign output respectively.
Further,
assume that the foreign economy is characterised by the same equations as the domestic
economy. The value of the multiplier in the domestic economy is:
